JOHANNESBURG - Foreign investors sold local shares worth R3.4bn on a net basis over the past week bringing the tally to R11.1bn so far in January marking a bumpy start to 2017.Foreigners were aggressive net sellers of local shares in 2016 having dished more than R100bn worth of local shares according to the JSE data.Net bond outflows were R1.1bn last week while net equity outflows for the month to date are about R719m.Nedbank Corporate and Investment Banking analysts said the widespread uncertainty around US policies following the inauguration of Donald Trump and other geopolitical tension had affected the portfolio flows. This is likely to persist over the medium term keeping foreign flows into our markets firmly on the back foot. iNet Bridge